snippet: The generational shift President Obama embodied is under way, but it will not change Washington as quickly as voters once hoped.
abstract: Political Times column; Pres Obama's victory is not accompanied by the same exceptional optimism and expectation of compromise that attended his victory in 2008, but it is still evidence of a generational shift in the electorate.
lead_paragraph: The generational shift President Obama embodied is under way, but it will not change Washington as quickly as voters once hoped.

headline.print_headline: Winning a Second Term, Obama Will Confront Familiar Headwinds
headline.seo: In Obama’s Second Term, Familiar Challenges
headline.main: Winning a Second Term, Obama Will Confront Familiar Headwinds
